node.text:
From the moment I could express myself, I gravitated towards mermaids. As a transgender girl I always felt a connection toward wanting to be a “mermaid” because they don’t have genitalia, they have a tail. After my 8th birthday, I even began creating mermaid tails to swim in the water like a mermaid. Today, I share with you my “Mermaids Tale” in collaboration with the Smithsonian’s @amhistorymuseum They have created a new exhibit called “Girlhood - It’s Complicated,” opening today, that examines the ways that girls have spoken up, challenged expectations and been on the frontlines of change. At the center of my girlhood will always be mermaids, so I hope you enjoy this deep dive into my journey ❤️ #BecauseOfHerStory #mermaidstale #mermaids #transgender 

—-
Thank you to my brother, @sander_54, for helping me edit and produce this video.

Our entire family is proud to support the fifth annual #JazzandFriends National Day of School and Community Readings.  Through the #IAmJazz children’s book, we hope to create a more inclusive and understanding environment for all kids in school! ❤️

node.text:
When I was 8 years old I was banned from playing girls’ soccer. During that time my family and I didn’t give up and finally, after over 2 years of advocating, the United States Soccer Federation passed a Trans-inclusive policy for all soccer players in our country. Now, almost 10 years later, it pains me to hear multiple states such as Idaho and Arizona could pass bills that ban trans girls from playing sports and subject all girls to invasive searches of their genitals, hormone checks and even genetic testing. As you see in this video, the pain my family went through was unbearable(One of the only times I’ve seen my dad cry towards the end of video) and no family should ever have to feel that way. We must stop these terrible bills! 
Arizona will be voting tomorrow morning on HB 2706 tell them to vote NO! Idaho already passed a bill through the House and it will soon move to the Idaho Senate. Tell Governor Little to veto HB 500 if it reaches his desk. 👏🏻

node.text: What would you do if you sat in a restaurant watching someone be bullied for being their authentic self. A few months ago, I appeared on “What would you do?” with @johnquinones where a woman was being harassed for using the female bathroom. Thankfully, as you will see in this clip, people stood up for the victim! Thank you to all of the allies and supporters in the community who stand up for the equal treatment, rights and protections of LGBTQ+ people! ❤️❤️

node.text: #2018 was a rough year in my life. I experienced a major complication with my gender confirmation surgery and wound up back in the OR one week after the initial procedure. It was a tough journey, but experiences like that one only make us stronger in the end. Though it can be hard at times, a positive mindset and the support of those around you can help you conquer any challenge. Thank you to all my fans who have supported me throughout the years! Love you all, this video is for you!💕#decadechallenge

node.text:
~𝔗𝔥𝔢 𝔈𝔫𝔠𝔥𝔞𝔫𝔱𝔯𝔢𝔰𝔰 ~

With her fluttering fingers and brilliant dazzle,
All were enamored by her relentless losing battle.

A beautiful black heart fighting to be free,
Her smile would blind all who could see.

Her cracked voice shouting like a dying siren’s song,
Killed all the listeners who felt they could belong.

But belong they cannot for the Enchantress is alone,
Separated from the beauty of the oneness that is home.

To help raise money for the charity, I am raffling off this rainbow tie-die dress that I created. So, how can you win?

Enter by sending Venmo to Sander_54 or a cashapp to $TransKids. The winner be announced tomorrow night around 9 pm EST on either a live video or my story! Good luck 🏳️‍🌈 #charitygiveaway
